HEADWORD: Planchet
<hw>Planch"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>planchette</ets> a small board, dim. of <ets>planche</ets>. See
<er>Planch</er>.]</ety> <def>A flat piece of metal; especially, a disk
of metal ready to be stamped as a coin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planchette</ent>⟦br⟧
